Package: SpatialDataR
Title: Native R Interface to the SpatialData Zarr Format for Spatial
    Omics
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R:
    person("CuiweiG", email = "48gaocuiwei@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides native R infrastructure for inspecting and
    reading SpatialData-formatted Zarr stores without Python
    dependencies. Discovers and lazily references images, labels,
    points, shapes, and annotation tables. Includes element-level
    readers for Zarr arrays (via Rarr/pizzarr), Parquet point
    tables (via arrow), and coordinate system transformations.
    Designed as a lightweight bridge between the Python SpatialData
    ecosystem and R/Bioconductor spatial analysis workflows.
License: Artistic-2.0
